option.name: content
option.value:
Generate a conventional git commit message using this format: <type>(<scope>): <description>
Rules: - Type must be one of: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore, ci, build - Scope is optional, in parentheses, describing section of codebase - Description must: - Be in imperative mood ("add" not "added") - Not be capitalized - Have no period at end - Be 50 chars or less
For breaking changes, add a footer with: BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
Example: feat(auth): add password reset endpoint
